news.title: Supertech twin towers: On Day 1, eight trucks clear 180 tonnes of debris
news.para: Officials of the demolition company, Edifice Engineering, said the trucks transported the debris from Sector 93A, where the towers had once stood, to the C&D plant in Sector 80 of Noida.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents protest over hike in BPTP upkeep fee
news.para: Spread across 43 acres of land, the township was developed in multiple phases with four residential societies namely Serene, Generations, Spacio and Terra.

news.title: IGE India buys two apartments in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 151 crore
news.para: The company has purchased both the apartments spread over a total of 16,072 sq ft on the 58th and 59th floors of the project from the developer, Oberoi Realty’s subsidiary Oasis Realty, that is executing the project.

news.title: Sunteck Realty acquires 7.25 acres land in Beverly Park, Mumbai
news.para: The project is estimated to have development potential of approx 2.5 million sq ft built up area and a revenue potential of around Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: Bengaluru: CID arrests Mantri Developers' director, son after complaints from buyers
news.para: Several homebuyers had filed complaints with Subramanyapura police stating that they were cheated of money by the builders, who had lured them with attractive offers, misleading brochures and fake schemes.

news.title: Cash-strapped Ludhiana civic body revises property tax target to Rs 130 crore
news.para: Officials claimed that they expect to recover at least Rs 60 crore by the month-end, for which they were organising special camps in commercial areas and industrial units.

news.title: Haryana: Error in property tax ID? Submit complaints via NDC
news.para: The civic body has also decided to form a separate NDC cell to immediately resolve property IDs-related grievances.

news.title: Mysuru: MUDA forms task force to control mushrooming illegal construction
news.para: The team of officials will visit the places where unauthorised construction of layouts is found. He added when it is found illegal, the layouts will be cleared by issuing them notices.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board allots 18,000 vacated flats under rehabilitation scheme
news.para: CHB has allotted about 18,000 flats under rehabilitation scheme, small flat scheme and affordable rental housing scheme. These flats have been allotted for the occupation of the allottee and their families.

news.title: Fractional ownership platform hBits raises Rs 20 crore from angel investors
news.para: The property technology company is planning to scale up various activities, including acquisition of new assets under management, customer acquisition and expansion of the business to newer cities.

news.title: MahaRERA, registration department data integration soon
news.para: State housing secretary Milind Mhaiskar said discussions on the integration of data were on. "We are working on it and the RERA and registration data will be integrated to ensure no violation of rules." he told TOI.

news.title: UP-RERA invites buyers to complete Antriksh Sanskriti projects in Ghaziabad
news.para: In June this year, the UP-Rera cancelled the registration of three real estate projects in Ghaziabad — Antriksh Sanskriti phases 2 and 3, and Raksha Vigyaan Sanskriti Phase 2, all located in the Pratap Vihar area — after the developers, even after repeated extensions, failed to complete construction.

news.title: Punjab: Online submission of applications to get NOCs for regularization of properties
news.para: Housing and Urban Development Minister Aman Arora said this facility of regularization could be availed only by those residents whose properties fall under the unauthorized colonies developed before March 19, 2018.

news.title: Registration of homes in Hyderabad region down 36% in August 2022: Report
news.para: In August 2021, 8,144 housing units were registered in the Hyderabad residential market that includes four districts -- Hyderabad, Medchal-Malkajgiri, Rangareddy and Sangareddy.

news.title: Bengaluru: Of 629 'faulty' buildings, notices issued to owners of 423 to raze structures
news.para: As per a survey, there are 629 ‘faulty’ buildings in the city. The maximum buildings are in south zone (216), followed by west (160), east (101), Yelahanka (84), Mahadevapura (37), Bommanahalli and Dasarahalli (11 each) and nine in RR Nagar.​
